n, interview, or presentation of student work.   Course List         Code  Title  Hours     Summary of Requirements  General Education Requirements 24  Degree and Track Course Requirements (vary by track) 35-44  General Track (35 hours)  Performance Track (44 hours)  Authorship Track (41 hours)  Electives (vary by track) 51-61  General Track (60-61 hours)  Performance Track (51-52 hours)  Authorship Track (54-55 hours)  DLG 120 UIC First-Year Dialogue Seminar (Required of new freshmen only) a 1  Total Hours 120   a Hours of electives required are based upon the track selected by students within the BA in Theatre and Performance, and whether they are required to complete DLG 120 for 1 hour (required of new freshmen only).  General Education Requirements   Course List         Code  Title  Hours     Required Courses  a  ENGL 160 Academic Writing I: Writing in Academic and Public Contexts 3  ENGL 161 Academic Writing II: Writing for Inquiry and Research 3  Exploring World Cultures course  b 3  Analyzing the Natural World course  b 3-5  Understanding the Individual and Society course  b 3  Understanding U.S. Society course  b 3  Additional General Education Core courses from any category  b 4-6  Total Hours 24   a The Understanding the Past and Understanding the Creative Arts General Education requirements are met by courses within the degree. b Students should consult the General Education section of the catalog for a list of approved courses in this category.  Theatre and Performance Degree and Track Course Requirements   Course List         Code  Title  Hours     Required Courses  Students in all tracks complete 20 hours of degree core course work:  THTR 101 Theatre History I: Premodern Drama a 3  THTR 141 Acting I: Fundamentals 3  THTR 182 Practicum in Theater: Run Crew 1  THTR 183 Practicum in Theater: Build Crew 1  THTR 201 Theatre History II: Modern Theatre b 3  THTR 217 Movement & Voice I 3  THTR 230 Script Analysis for Theatrical Production 3  THTR 448 The Business of Theatre: A Career in the Arts 3  Required Courses by Track (hours vary by track) 3-12  General Track—Required Courses  THTR 241 Acting II: Scene Study  Performance Track—Required Courses  THTR 241 Acting II: Scene Study  THTR 317 Movement & Voice II  THTR 341 Acting III: Classics  THTR 449 Capstone: Senior Project  Authorship Track—Required Courses  THTR 449 Capstone: Senior Project  Selectives (hours vary by track) 12-18  All tracks select one of the following three Design, Production, and Technology sequences:  THTR 150 Fundamental of Theatre Technology  THTR 151 Costume Technology I: Introduction to Costume Technology  or THTR 152 Lighting Technology I: An Introduction to Lighting Tech  or THTR 153 Scenic Technology I: An Introduction to Stagecraft for the Theatre  OR  THTR 155 Fundamentals of Theatre Design b  THTR 156 Lighting Design I: An Introduction to Lighting Design  or THTR 158 Costume Design I  or THTR 170 Sound Design: An Introduction to Sound Design for Theatre  or THTR 250 Scenic Design I  or THTR 259 Makeup Design  OR  THTR 150 Fundamental of Theatre Technology  THTR 155 Fundamentals of Theatre Design  THTR 250 Scenic Design I  THTR 259 Makeup Design  Authorship Selectives:  General and Performance Tracks—Select two courses from the following list.  Authorship Track—Select four courses from the following list.  THTR 240 Improvisation for the Actor  THTR 331 Page to Stage: Adaptation of Text for Theatrical Performance  THTR 332 Performance Ethnography  THTR 333 Stage Direction  THTR 431 Playwriting  THTR 435 Contemporary Performance Techniques  Total Hours 35-44   a This course is approved for the Understanding the Past General Education category or the Understanding the Creative Arts General Education category. b This course is approved for the Understanding the Creative Arts General Education category.  Electives   Course List         Code  Title  Hours     Electives  Electives to reach total hours  a 51-61  Total Hours 51-61   a Hours of ele